_comment: * 'key' is an internal category name, 'name' is the English category name, and 'emojis' is
an array of file names (with extensions) in the public/emojis directory
* Ideally category names would support translation but they do not due to a bug with the emoji picker.
* The order of the categories in this file, as well as the order of the emojis in each category, is respected.
* An emoji which is defined in two categories will display in both without issue.
This is useful if an emoji could appear in two categories,
and for displaying emojis in the 'New Emojis' category as well as their original one.
* If an emoji is given the same name as a default one, it won't function properly.
generally, try to keep everything lowercase.
sequential emojis should be the same name, numbered in order. Two-part emojis may be signified with -l/-r or -1/-2.
name: New Emojis
A Hog with Shit on its Testicles
